# O-Walkie Project Memory

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Go relay server (`backend/cmd/relay/main.go`), WebSocket control + UDP audio data.
- Android client: Kotlin, foreground `WalkieService`, Opus via `kopus`, Gradle Kotlin DSL.
- Windows client: C++ wxWidgets (`windows-client-cpp`), Boost.Beast, **miniaudio** (vendored), Opus (legacy C# WPF removed).
- Audio protocol: Opus mono, server handshake with protocol/version/audio params.

## Current Task
- Android: adaptive UDP keepalive (foreground vs background intervals/timeouts) remains in `WalkieService`; monitor battery/NAT behavior after ANR fix (receive timeout applied on `Dispatchers.IO` only).
- Windows: `windows-client-cpp` — server profiles (`profiles.json`), audio in `audio.json`, migration from legacy `connection.json`; auto-reconnect with backoff after WS/UDP loss until user Disconnect; `RelayClient` avoids self-join deadlock and uses connection-lost callback + `JoinWorkerThreads`.
- Accessibility / background hardware PTT removed from Android for Play Protect compatibility; foreground PTT preserved.

## Recent Key Changes
- Android: fixed crash on network handoff (`StackOverflowError`) by breaking recursive recovery loop between `recreateUdpSocket()` and `sendUdpKeepalivePacket()`; keepalive send from recreate path now skips nested recovery call.
- Windows: `windows-client-cpp` `RelayClient::Connect` — UDP remote endpoint берётся из `tcp::socket::remote_endpoint()` (тот же адрес, что и WS), сокет UDP открывается v4/v6 в соответствии; убран `make_address(host)` на этапе UDP (исправление WSAEINVAL для имён вроде `localhost`).
- Android: fixed potential Activity resume ANR by moving UDP socket timeout policy update (`soTimeout`) off the service main thread to `Dispatchers.IO`.
- Windows: C++ wxWidgets client persists last connection fields to `%AppData%`-style user data dir as `connection.json` (host/ports/channel/repeater); app/vendor display names set for stable config path.
- Windows: `windows-client-cpp` — miniaudio вместо PortAudio; выбор устройств ввода/вывода, сохранение индексов в `connection.json`; POST_BUILD кладёт exe и UCRT64 DLL в `build/dist/` (`scripts/bundle-ucrt64-deps.sh`, кэш `OWALKIE_MSYS_ROOT`).
- Windows client: reduced UDP keepalive aggressiveness to `5s` with ±15% jitter to lower synchronized keepalive bursts while preserving simple desktop networking behavior.
- Android: tuned background idle battery mode further — `UDP_BG_KEEPALIVE_IDLE_INTERVAL_SEC=50`, `UDP_RECV_TIMEOUT_BACKGROUND_MS=10000`, cached signal-strength polling in background (max once per 50s), immediate keepalive mode switch on app focus change.
- Android: reduce background battery use (softer UDP keepalive when app not in focus, longer RX socket timeout in background), bind UDP `DatagramSocket` to `ConnectivityManager` active `Network` after handoffs, queue UDP socket recreation until end of TX/call/roger, reset Opus on new `sessionId` and fix playback loop race on reconnect.
- Implemented server-side configurable Opus parameters (bitrate/complexity/FEC/DTX/application) and handshake propagation.
- Added and refined idle squelch shot scheduler on server:
  - timer random `10..squelch_shots` seconds (when idle),
  - shot duration random `tail_min_ms..tail_max_ms`,
  - 1s silence before and after shot.
- Changed relay startup config behavior:
  - default uses `./config.json`,
  - optional config path via first CLI argument.
- Removed Android Accessibility service path and background hardware PTT flow:
  - deleted `PttAccessibilityService`,
  - removed manifest/xml declarations and related strings/UI/settings logic.

